{:proof/problem-id "apm-a93A03", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\nTARGET SANITY CHECK — mentions-problem-objects? ✅ (plan/alignment work on weak convergence of \\(h_n\\) in a Hilbert space, inner products, and norms) · avoids-assuming-conclusion? ✅ (the Lean target states both claims as implications without presuming them) · meaningful-without-prose? ✅ (the combined theorem is a standalone Hilbert-space fact). Notes: Mathlib has inner-product norm identities; stitching them with weak convergence will need custom work.\n\n```\nPROOF-PLAN.EDN\n{:goal \"Use the weak-limit identities ⟨h_n,h⟩ → ⟨h,h⟩ to derive norm convergence and the liminf inequality in a Hilbert space.\"\n :terms [{:name \"weak convergence\"\n          :meaning \"For every k ∈ H, ⟨h_n, k⟩ → ⟨h, k⟩.\"\n          :needed-because \"Plugging k = h (or k = h_n − h) provides the key inner-product limits.\"}\n         {:name \"norm identity\"\n          :meaning \"‖u − v‖² = ‖u‖² + ‖v‖² − 2 Re⟨u, v⟩ in a real or complex Hilbert space.\"\n          :needed-because \"This expands ‖h_n − h‖² in terms of quantities whose limits we control.\"}\n         {:name \"liminf control\"\n          :meaning \"The inequality in (b) follows from taking liminf on both sides of the norm identity without assuming norm convergence.\"\n          :needed-because \"Part (b) generalizes part (a) and supplies the foundation for the contradiction argument.\"}]\n :strategy [{:id :s1\n             :formal-dependency \"HilbertSpace.norm_sq_sub_eq\"\n             :informal-dependency \"Use weak convergence with k = h to show ⟨h_n,h⟩ → ‖h‖²; combine with the norm identity to prove (a) and (b).\"\n             :why-this-now \"Both parts reduce to algebraic manipulations of the same identity once the inner-product limits are known.\"\n             :lean-target \"A Lean lemma showing that weak convergence plus norm convergence implies strong convergence, together with the liminf inequality.\"\n             :mathlib-status \"Mathlib already has inner-product expansions; the weak-limit facts may need modest glue code.\"}]\n :stage-status {:stage1 :done :stage2 :done :stage3 :in-progress :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n```\nFORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n{:main-claim {:informal-claim \"In a Hilbert space, weak convergence plus convergence of norms implies strong convergence, and weak limits have norm at most the liminf of the norms.\"\n              :formal-name \"weak_conv_norm_conv_strong\"\n              :formal-target \"theorem weak_conv_norm_conv_strong {H} [InnerProductSpace ℝ H] {h hₙ : ℕ → H} ... : (hₙ ⇀ h ∧ ‖hₙ‖ → ‖h‖) → hₙ →ᵣ h ∧ ‖h‖ ≤ liminf ‖hₙ‖\"\n              :sanity-check {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n                             :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n                             :meaningful-without-prose? true\n                             :notes \"Combines both parts (a) and (b) into a single statement about weak limits.\"}}\n :alignments [{:formal-name \"weak_conv_norm_conv_strong\"\n               :formal-statement \"Weak convergence + norm convergence ⇒ strong convergence (part a) and liminf inequality (part b).\"\n               :informal-clause \"Both sentences proved in Stage 1.\"\n               :role :main-theorem}\n              {:formal-name \"norm_square_expansion\"\n               :formal-statement \"‖u − v‖² = ‖u‖² + ‖v‖² − 2 Re ⟨u,v⟩.\"\n               :informal-clause \"Used to expand ‖hₙ − h‖².\"\n               :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n- Stage 1 now gives the full Hilbert-space argument (weak + norm convergence ⇒ strong convergence and the liminf inequality) plus the sanity pass and “what connects”; see `execute.md:1-24`.\n- Stage 2 lists the supporting lemmas—weak convergence, the norm-square expansion, and limit arithmetic—matching the single strategy item in `proof-plan.edn` (`execute.md:26-34`).\n- Stage 3 records the Lean blocker (missing `weak_conv_norm_conv_strong` in Mathlib) and Stage 4 marks that polarization/limit sentence as the outstanding informal step (`execute.md:36-46`); `Main.lean` remains boilerplate.\n- `proof-plan.edn`, `formal-alignment.edn`, and `changelog.edn` are populated with the required structure and metadata.", :proof/extraction {:phases {}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :proved, :phase-count 0, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A93A03/Apm_v2_a93A03_1775049613401", :frame/id "apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T13:20:13.425128Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A93A03.Apm_v2_a93A03_1775049613401", :proof/problem-id "a93A03", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a93A03/apm-v2-a93A03-1775049613401/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A93A03/Apm_v2_a93A03_1775049613401/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A93A03/Apm_v2_a93A03_1775049613401/Scratch.lean"}}, :proof/artifacts ["/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A93A03/Apm_v2_a93A03_1775049613401/Main.lean" "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A93A03/Apm_v2_a93A03_